President Joe Biden has announced his intention to nominate Melanie Egorin as Assistant Secretary for Legislation at the Department of Health and Human Services. Egorin has 25 years of health policy experience, including over 15 years with the federal government. She currently serves as the Deputy Staff Director for the Health Subcommittee and professional tax staff for the Committee on Ways and Means in the U.S. House of Representatives. Egorin has expertise in federal health programs and the American health system, and has worked on various public payer health policy issues throughout her career. She is known for her collaborative workstyle, bipartisan leadership, and mentorship. Egorin holds Bachelor's and Master's degrees from Emory University and a Ph.D. from the University of California San Francisco. She resides in Washington, D.C. with her husband, two children, and dog.